Overview
The Flask Weather Dashboard is a web application that fetches live weather forecast data from the OpenWeatherMap API and displays it in a browser. It uses Flask for backend logic, Jinja2 for templating, and Chart.js for visualization. The app shows temperature trends for the next several hours in a line chart.

Features
Fetches real-time weather forecast data from OpenWeatherMap.

Extracts temperature and time slots for the next 24 hours.

Displays the data in a responsive line chart.

Provides a quick visual overview of temperature changes throughout the day.

